  "prompt": "How do I know if he is interested in love or lust?",
  "response": "Determining whether someone is interested in love or lust can be nuanced, but there are key signs and behaviors to look for:\n\n### **Signs of Love:**\n1. **Emotional Investment**  \n   - Shows genuine care for your feelings, well-being, and happiness.  \n   - Makes an effort to understand you on a deeper level.  \n\n2. **Long-Term Focus**  \n   - Talks about future plans or includes you in their long-term goals.  \n   - Is patient and willing to build a relationship over time.  \n\n3. **Respect and Support**  \n   - Respects your boundaries and values.  \n   - Supports your goals, dreams, and personal growth.  \n\n4. **Consistency**  \n   - Their interest in you is steady and not just based on physical interactions.  \n   - They prioritize spending quality time with you, even when physical intimacy isn\u2019t involved.  \n\n5. **Open Communication**  \n   - Expresses their feelings openly and honestly.  \n   - Discusses their intentions and wants to understand yours.  \n\n---\n\n### **Signs of Lust:**  \n1. **Physical Focus**  \n   - Primarily interested in physical attraction and sexual chemistry.  \n   - Compliments are centered on your appearance rather than your personality.  \n\n2. **Short-Term Mindset**  \n   - Avoids discussions about the future or commitment.  \n   - Shows interest mainly in spending time together in private or intimate settings.  \n\n3. **Lack of Emotional Connection**  \n   - Doesn\u2019t show much curiosity about your thoughts, feelings, or life.  \n   - Acts distant or uninterested when physical intimacy isn\u2019t the focus.  \n\n4. **Inconsistency**  \n   - Their interest fluctuates based on convenience or availability.  \n   - They may disappear or become less attentive after physical intimacy.  \n\n5. **Surface-Level Interaction**  \n   - Conversations stay shallow and don\u2019t delve into deeper topics.  \n   - They may avoid introducing you to friends or family.  \n\n---\n\n### **What You Can Do:**\n- **Observe Their Actions:** Actions often speak louder than words. Pay attention to how they treat you in different situations.  \n- **Communicate Directly:** Have an honest conversation about their intentions and what they\u2019re looking for in the relationship.  \n- **Take Your Time:** Love often develops gradually, while lust tends to be more immediate. Don\u2019t rush into anything before you feel confident about their intentions.  \n\nUltimately, trust your instincts. If something feels off or doesn\u2019t align with what you\u2019re looking for, it\u2019s okay to reassess the relationship.",
